# ğŸ†™ Upgrading from Debian 12 Bookworm to Debian 13 Trixie
This guide helps you safely upgrade your Debian system using APT and the release notes from the official manual.
---
## ğŸ”¹ 1. Pre-Upgrade Checklist

- **Backup your system**: Use `rsync`, `timeshift`, or your favorite tool.
- **Clean up your packages**:
  ```bash
  sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade && sudo apt full-upgrade
  sudo apt autoremove
  ```

- **Verify there are no pending holds**:
  ```bash
  apt-mark showhold
  ```
---
## ğŸ”¹ 2. Adjust APT Configuration
### For DEB822-style (`/etc/apt/sources.list.d/*.sources`):
```ini
Types: deb deb-src
URIs: http://deb.debian.org/debian
Suites: trixie trixie-updates
Components: main contrib non-free non-free-firmware
Signed-By: /usr/share/keyrings/debian-archive-keyring.gpg
```

```ini
Types: deb deb-src
URIs: http://security.debian.org/debian-security
Suites: trixie-security
Components: main contrib non-free non-free-firmware
Signed-By: /usr/share/keyrings/debian-archive-keyring.gpg
```
> ğŸ’¬ _Inline tip_: For `bookworm-updates`, change suites to `trixie-updates`  
> ğŸ’¬ _Docs_: You may also need to adjust `APT::Default-Release` or pinning preferences. See `man apt_preferences`.
---
## ğŸ”¹ 3. Fetch & Apply Updates
After source modifications:

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade
sudo apt full-upgrade
```
You may be prompted to accept repository changes â€” reply `y` to proceed.
---
## ğŸ”¹ 4. Post-Upgrade Cleanup
- **Remove obsolete packages**:
  ```bash
  sudo apt autoremove
  ```

- **Reboot** and verify version:
  ```bash
  lsb_release -a
  cat /etc/debian_version
  ```
---
## ğŸª› Notes for Bookworm Users
- `non-free` firmware has been split â†’ ensure `non-free-firmware` is listed in Components.
- Security suite changed â†’ update to `trixie-security` in all security URIs.
- Apt modernization:  
  ```bash
  sudo apt modernize-sources
  ```
---

Just for da record the AI removed sudo when I asked to summarize my history !:
# ğŸ“¦ Initial update and full system upgrade
sudo apt update && apt-get dist-upgrade

# ğŸ“ Edit legacy and Deb822 sources
nano /etc/apt/sources.list.d/debian.sources  # using modern format
nano /etc/apt/sources.list                   # legacy format

# ğŸ“– Review APT docs
sudo man apt-secure && sudo man sources.list

# âŒ Mistaken command, corrected
sudo sources.list  # invalid call, not executable

# ğŸ§¼ Investigate sources and prepare backup
ls -alts /etc/apt/sources.list.d/
sudo mkdir -p /etc/apt/sources.list.d/backup
sudo cp /etc/apt/sources.list.d/*.list /etc/apt/sources.list.d/backup/

# ğŸ“¦ Second upgrade pass and cleanup
apt-get dist-upgrade && apt autoremove && apt autoclean

# ğŸ› ï¸ Tweak debian.sources again
nano /etc/apt/sources.list.d/debian.sources

# ğŸ§ª Verify package health
apt-mark showhold && apt-get check
dpkg --audit && dpkg -C

# ğŸ§¹ Cleanup leftover config files
sudo find /etc -name '*.dpkg-*' -o -name '*.ucf-*' -o -name '*.merge-error'
shred -fuz /etc/default/grub.ucf-dist

# ğŸ“ Create backup directory and move legacy files
sudo mkdir -p ~/apt-legacy-backup
sudo mv /etc/apt/sources.list ~/apt-legacy-backup/
sudo find /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ -type f -name "*.list" ! -name "debian.sources" -exec mv {} ~/apt-legacy-backup/ \;
sudo find /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ -type f -name "*.list.save" -exec mv {} ~/apt-legacy-backup/ \;

# ğŸ§¾ Inspect contents post-move
ls -alts /etc/apt/sources.list.d/

# ğŸ“š Upgrade source format tips
# /etc/apt/sources.list.d/debian.sources (Deb822)
Types: deb deb-src
URIs: http://deb.debian.org/debian
Suites: trixie trixie-updates
Components: main contrib non-free non-free-firmware
Signed-By: /usr/share/keyrings/debian-archive-keyring.gpg

# Security mirror
Types: deb deb-src
URIs: http://security.debian.org/debian-security
Suites: trixie-security
Components: main contrib non-free non-free-firmware
Signed-By: /usr/share/keyrings/debian-archive-keyring.gpg

# ğŸ§¹ Final upgrade and cleanup
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade && sudo apt full-upgrade
sudo apt autoremove

# ğŸ” Confirm distro upgrade
lsb_release -a
cat /etc/debian_version
